from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import requests
import numpy as np
import time

Hotelname = [] 
price = []
rating = []
Type1 = []
original_price = []
Discount = []
pagenum =[]



total_time = time.time()

for i in range(1, 151): 
    start_time = time.time() 
    URL = f"https://www.eazydiner.com/restaurants?location=delhi-ncr&page={i}"
    page = requests.get(URL)
    soup = BeautifulSoup(page.text, "html.parser")

    for x in soup.find_all('div', attrs={'class':'relative pointer listing_touch_box__00o7f'}):
        hotelname = x.find('a', attrs={'class':'ellipsis listing_res_name__uVIN8'})
        cost = x.find('div', attrs={'class':'flex align-v-center'})   # discounted price
        rat = x.find("tspan")
        type1 = x.find('div', attrs={'class':'flex align-v-center ellipsis listing_multi_cuisines__zLLXK'})
        op = x.find('div', attrs={'class':'flex align-v-center'})
        discount = x.find('div', attrs={'class':'ellipsis listing_offer_text__LXKw1'})
        

        Hotelname.append(hotelname.text if hotelname else np.nan)
        price.append(cost.text if cost else np.nan)
        rating.append(rat.text if rat else np.nan)
        Type1.append(type1.text if type1 else np.nan)
        original_price.append(op.text if op else np.nan)
        Discount.append(discount.text if discount else np.nan)
          
        
        pagenum.append(i)


    print(f'Page {i} completed in {time.time()-start_time:.2f} seconds')

print("Total Time Completed in seconds", str(time.time()-total_time))

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

plt.style.use("seaborn-v0_8-whitegrid")

# Ensure numeric columns
df['Price'] = pd.to_numeric(df['Price'], errors='coerce')
df['Rating'] = pd.to_numeric(df['Rating'], errors='coerce')

# ----- Choose categorical & numerical columns -----
cat_col = "Hotel_name"    # categorical column
num_col = "Price"         # numerical column

# ----- Keep only top 10 categories -----
top_categories = df[cat_col].value_counts().nlargest(10).index
df_top = df[df[cat_col].isin(top_categories)]

# ----- Create plots -----
fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(14, 10))
fig.suptitle(f"Categorical vs Numerical Analysis (Top 10 {cat_col})", fontsize=16, color="blue")

# 1 Box Plot
sns.boxplot(data=df_top, x=cat_col, y=num_col, ax=axes[0,0], palette="Set2")
axes[0,0].set_title("Box Plot")
axes[0,0].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)

# 2 Violin Plot
sns.violinplot(data=df_top, x=cat_col, y=num_col, ax=axes[0,1], palette="Set3")
axes[0,1].set_title("Violin Plot")
axes[0,1].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)

# 3 Histogram
sns.histplot(data=df_top, x=num_col, hue=cat_col, multiple="stack", ax=axes[1,0], kde=False)
axes[1,0].set_title("Histogram")

# 4 KDE Plot
sns.kdeplot(data=df_top, x=num_col, hue=cat_col, fill=True, common_norm=False, ax=axes[1,1])
axes[1,1].set_title("KDE Plot")

plt.tight_layout(rect=[0, 0, 1, 0.96])
save_path = r"D:\webscraping project\bivariate(web).png"
plt.savefig(save_path, dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Select categorical column
cat_col = "Type"   # change this to your column name

# Count category occurrences
category_counts = df[cat_col].value_counts()

# Keep only top N and group the rest as "Others"
top_n = 8
if len(category_counts) > top_n:
    top_categories = category_counts[:top_n]
    others = pd.Series({'Others': category_counts[top_n:].sum()})
    category_counts = pd.concat([top_categories, others])

# Plot the pie chart
plt.figure(figsize=(4,4))
colors = plt.cm.Paired.colors  # better balanced palette

plt.pie(
    category_counts,
    labels=category_counts.index,
    autopct='%1.1f%%',
    startangle=140,
    counterclock=False,
    colors=colors[:len(category_counts)],
    textprops={'fontsize': 10}
)

plt.title(f"Distribution of {cat_col} (Top {top_n} Categories)", fontsize=14, color='blue')
plt.tight_layout()
save_path = r"D:\webscraping project\piechart(web).png"
plt.savefig(save_path, dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')
plt.show()

cat1 = "Type"
cat2 = "Hotel_name"
# -----------------------------

# Optional: Keep only top 10 categories for better readability
top_cat1 = df[cat1].value_counts().nlargest(10).index
top_cat2 = df[cat2].value_counts().nlargest(8).index
df_filtered = df[df[cat1].isin(top_cat1) & df[cat2].isin(top_cat2)]

# Grouped count data
grouped_counts = df_filtered.groupby([cat1, cat2]).size().reset_index(name="Count")

# --- 1 Grouped Bar Chart ---
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 6))
sns.barplot(data=grouped_counts, x=cat1, y="Count", hue=cat2, palette="Set2")
plt.title(f"Grouped Bar Chart: {cat1} vs {cat2}", fontsize=14, color="blue")
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.legend(title=cat2, bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
plt.tight_layout()
save_path = r"D:\webscraping project\bivariate3(web).png"
plt.savefig(save_path, dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')
plt.show()

# --- 2 Categorical Heatmap ---
cross_tab = pd.crosstab(df_filtered[cat1], df_filtered[cat2])

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.heatmap(cross_tab, annot=True, fmt="d", cmap="YlGnBu")
plt.title(f"Categorical Heatmap: {cat1} vs {cat2}", fontsize=14, color="blue")
plt.xlabel(cat2)
plt.ylabel(cat1)
plt.tight_layout()
save_path = r"D:\webscraping project\bivariate2(web).png"
plt.savefig(save_path, dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')
plt.show()
